Packages to be installed on a fresh version of Ubuntu 10.10:
sudo aptitude install subversion automake libtool g++ libgsl0-dev python-numpy python-ply libboost-python-dev mercurial libgtkmm-2.4-dev libgtkglextmm-x11-1.2-dev libhdf5-serial-dev

Steps to install E-Cell System v3:
cd
mkdir wrk
cd wrk
svn co http://ecell.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/ecell/ecell3/trunk ecell3svn
cd ecell3svn
./autogen.sh
./configure --prefix=$HOME/root
make -j3
make install (files will be installed in the $HOME/root directory)
gedit .bashrc
  add the following at the bottom
      export PATH=$HOME/root/bin:$PATH
      export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/root/lib:$HOME/wrk/ecell3-spatiocyte:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:.
      export PYTHONPATH=$HOME/root/lib/python:$HOME/root/lib/python2.6/site-packages:$HOME/src/epdp:$PYTHONPATH
      export ECELL3_DM_PATH=.
source ~/.bashrc

Try running a simple model:
ecell3-session-monitor (try opening it, and then close it)
cd $HOME/wrk/ecell3svn/doc/samples/simple/
ecell3-em2eml simple.em
ecell3-session-monitor -f simple.eml

Steps to install E-Cell3-Spatiocyte:
cd $HOME/wrk
hg clone http://t1.gsc.riken.jp/hg/ecell3-spatiocyte
cd ecell3-spatiocyte
make -j3

Steps to run E-Cell3-Spatiocyte MinDE model:
cp $HOME/wrk/ecell3-spatiocyte/samples/2010.arjunan.syst.synth.biol.wt.em $HOME/wrk/ecell3-spatiocyte/
cd $HOME/wrk/ecell3-spatiocyte/
ecell3-em2eml 2010.arjunan.syst.synth.biol.wt.em
ecell3-sessiom-monitor
load the model 2010.arjunan.syst.synth.biol.wt.eml and run

to create a lossless movie:
ffmpeg -i image%07d.png -vcodec ffv1 -sameq test.avi
ffmpeg -i image%07d.png -vcodec huffyuv test.avi
mencoder "mf://*.png" -mf type=png:fps=30 -ovc xvid -xvidencopts fixed_quant=1 -o outputXvid.mov
